# Owensfield Community Platform — Master Pack v1 (Single Review Document)

**Purpose of this file:** one place containing (1) platform rules/spec, (2) roles & permissions, (3) workflows, (4) UI layout contract, (5) implementation checkpoints.  
**Editing rule:** if something is wrong, edit this file. Do not re-explain in chat.

---

## 0) Hard Non-Negotiables

- No discussion facility (no forum/comments/debate threads).
- Archive-first: things are **archived, not deleted**, unless explicitly stated otherwise (and even then, “delete” typically means archive + retain references).
- Governance changes require a poll and apply automatically on approval; logged and archived.

---

## 1) User States and Access Gates

### 1.1 User states
- Public (not logged in)
- Member (Inactive)
- Member (Active)
- RG Member (Representative Group)
- RG Member with **Elected Role** (Chair/Vice Chair/Secretary/Treasurer)
- Temporary Mode Authority (Chair and/or Vice Chair when RG < 4)

### 1.2 Inactive member restrictions (confirmed)
- Inactive members are **not available to member content**.
- Inactive members can access only:
  - Profile
  - Renewal/reactivation
- Everything else must be blocked.

---

## 2) Plots, Membership, Voting (Confirmed Rules)

### 2.1 Plots and voting value
- Number of plots is fixed.
- Each plot has **fixed voting value = 1**.

### 2.2 Split of voting value
The plot’s value (1) is split equally between all **active** people registered with the plot:
- 1–2 plot owners
- + 1 or more tenants
Inactive users contribute **0** (do not receive a share).

### 2.3 Joined plots (UPDATED)
- **More than two plots can be joined** and managed under **one membership**.
- Joining is assignable by RG admin.
- Voting value for a joined membership = sum of joined plots (e.g., 3 plots → value 3), split equally across all **active** registered people on that joined membership.

---

## 3) Membership Lifecycle (Confirmed)

- Membership renews annually from **scheduled AGM → next AGM**.
- Suggested membership fee exists but is not compulsory.
- Members are Active or Inactive depending on reactivation/renewal status.
- Only Active members can:
  - Vote
  - Suggest polls
  - Self-nominate for RG roles

---

## 4) Representative Group (RG) Structure (Confirmed)

### 4.1 RG membership size
- RG requires **4–7 members**.
- If RG falls below 4 → **Temporary Mode** until restored to ≥ 4.

### 4.2 Required RG roles
All 4 positions are required:
- Chair (single)
- Vice Chair (single)
- Treasurer (up to 2)
- Secretary (up to 2)

Same person can hold multiple roles if required (not preferred).

### 4.3 Temporary Mode (Critical)
Triggered when RG < 4:
- Chair and/or Vice Chair gets full governance access and may authorise/override procedures.
- Purpose: avoid deadlock/system breakdown until RG returns to ≥ 4.

---

## 5) Approval Thresholds (Confirmed)

- Minimum 4 RG members to approve:
  - Activating polls
  - Approving minutes, meetings, actions, communications, most governance/admin approvals
- 1 RG member required:
  - Accepting a heritage document submission
- 100% RG required:
  - Removal of an RG member

---

## 6) Pages and Modules (Functional Specification)

### 6.1 Communications (Confirmed)
Member view:
- Read-only archive for active members.

RG workflow:
- RG creates a communication thread.
- RG adds updates to the thread.
- RG can attach files to thread and updates.
- Thread remains active until closed, then archived.

### 6.2 Finance (Confirmed)
Active members:
- View only (account summary).

Treasurer:
- Only treasurer(s) can upload/add finance entries.

### 6.3 Documents (Confirmed + additional)
- Accessible to active members.
- Read-only for members.
- RG members can upload documents into specific folders.
- Archived documents can be edited/deleted only with **4 RG approvals**.
- General rule: archive, not delete.

### 6.4 Governance (Confirmed)
- Shows current governance settings and recent changes.
- Shows governance polls that are live (current vs proposed).
- Any governance change requires a poll.
- Approved governance change:
  - automatically takes effect
  - displayed on governance dashboard
  - recorded in governance log
  - stored in documents archive

### 6.5 Polls (Confirmed)
- Any active member can suggest a poll → goes to RG pending approvals.
- 4 RG approvals required to activate.
- Default runtime 2 weeks; no fixed rule on runtime; RG can close unresolved polls.
- Closed polls remain visible in “recent polls” and are archived in Documents.

### 6.6 Meetings (Confirmed)
- Community meetings: quarterly (3) + 1 AGM.
- Meetings can be scheduled but not required.
- RG meetings: scheduled by RG, visible to active members.

Meeting creation workflow:
- RG creates meeting
- Draft agenda auto-generated
- Draft minutes auto-generated
- Drafts editable (RG)
- Submitted drafts go into Pending Approval
- Once approved by RG, visible to members

Community agenda items:
- When agenda exists, members can submit agenda item via form/button
- Submission requires RG approval
- Approved item is added to agenda

### 6.7 Actions (Confirmed)
- Actions can be created and attached to: minutes, meetings, communications, polls
- RG records progress of an action
- Once marked complete → archived

### 6.8 Noticeboard / Calendar (Confirmed)
- Active members and RG members can create a calendar entry
- Visible to all members

---

## 7) RG Admin Area (Confirmed)

### 7.1 RG “Representative Group” page (RG-only)
- Pending elections
- List of current members and roles
- Link to role description document
- Volunteer button → request appears in “Pending approvals” admin tab
- Past members list (document stored automatically when someone steps down/elected)

### 7.2 When a member holds an elected role (Elected-RG tools)
Only RG members who hold an elected role can:
- access membership database
- update member profile details / edit profiles
- access admin tools relating to plots

Only treasurer can upload to finance.

### 7.3 Pending approvals (RG admin menu)
A single place where items awaiting required approvals appear (poll activation, meeting/agenda/minutes approvals, etc.).

---

## 8) Membership Database and Plot Registry (Confirmed)

Membership database should show:
- Plot details
- Residents (owners/tenants)
- Active or not
- Email address

Actions available (Elected-RG only):
- Edit profile
- Reset password
- Delete profile (special meaning: removes user details only)
  - Plot remains in database
  - Plot marked “unregistered member”
  - Can only be reinstated by plot owner contacting RG externally

Plot owner assignment:
- RG role members can assign a new registered plot owner to a plot
- “Plot owner” = physical building/plot owner
- RG must confirm in real life (meet/know externally) — not via platform trust

---

## 9) Elections and Role Changes (Confirmed)

- Elections can take place anytime.
- Role changes take effect only at:
  - OCG meeting or AGM
- If someone steps down, change comes into effect at that time as well.
- If uncontested nominations → automatically elected.
- Nomination length and election run time are editable.
- Elected role only comes into effect when position is free.

---

## 10) Annual Report (Confirmed)

- Auto-generated the day before next scheduled AGM meeting.
- Summarises data from previous AGM → that date:
  - spending/finances
  - total votes
  - polls
  - member details
  - main events/happenings
- Attached to AGM meeting and archived into AGM folder.

---

